{{efn-ua|name=UnderAgeStats|Wood's [[New Zealand Football]] profile as of 15 August 2012 (after the [[Football at the 2012 Summer Olympics|2012 Olympics]]) gave him 3 [[New Zealand national under-17 football team|under-17]] appearances without scoring, and 5 [[New Zealand men's national under-23 football team|under-23]] appearances with 1 goal,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nzfootball.co.nz/index.php?id=1125 |title=Chris Wood |publisher=New Zealand Football |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120815115616/http://www.nzfootball.co.nz/index.php?id=1125 |archive-date=15 August 2012}}</ref> made up of two warm-up friendlies,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oceaniafootball.com/ofc/News/ViewArticle/tabid/125/Article/a60d849c-0013-4971-b4e2-f1ad5d598dc0/language/en-US/Default.aspx |title=Oly Whites downed by Korea in friendly |publisher=Oceania Football Confederation |date=15 July 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130214114053/http://www.oceaniafootball.com/ofc/News/ViewArticle/tabid/125/Article/a60d849c-0013-4971-b4e2-f1ad5d598dc0/language/en-US/Default.aspx |archive-date=14 February 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oceaniafootball.com/ofc/News/ViewArticle/tabid/125/Article/25d132fe-373b-4329-be7b-9a717adf6a43/language/en-US/Default.aspx |title=Oly Whites defeated by UAE in Austria |publisher=Oceania Football Confederation |date=20 July 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303221806/http://www.oceaniafootball.com/ofc/News/ViewArticle/tabid/125/Article/25d132fe-373b-4329-be7b-9a717adf6a43/language/en-US/Default.aspx |archive-date=3 March 2016}}</ref> and three [[Football at the 2012 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament – Group C|2012 Olympics group matches]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rsssf.org/tablesn/nz-u23-intres.html |title=New Zealand – U-23 International Matches |first=Andre |last=Zlotkowski |date=1 October 2015 |publisher=Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation |access-date=28 July 2021}}</ref>

He was not in the squad for any match between 2012 and 2020 as per the full list of U23 matches at ''UltimateNZSoccer.com'':<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ultimatenzsoccer.com/NZRepSoccer/id158.htm |title=OlyWhites |website=UltimateNZSoccer.com |access-date=28 July 2021}}</ref> namely, the [[Football at the 2015 Pacific Games|2015 Pacific Games]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/football/nz-teams/114057291/road-to-tokyo-olympics-begins-for-new-zealand-under23-mens-football-team |title=Road to Tokyo Olympics begins for New Zealand under-23 men's football team |first=Andrew |last=Voerman |website=[[Stuff (website)|Stuff]] |date=7 July 2019 |access-date=28 July 2021}}</ref> the [[Football at the 2019 Pacific Games|2019 Pacific Games]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nzfootball.co.nz/newsarticle/78844 |title=Promising U-23 group heading to Samoa |publisher=New Zealand Football |date=1 July 2019 |access-date=28 July 2021}}</ref> and the 2019 friendlies against Australia and [[2019 OFC Men's Olympic Qualifying Tournament|Olympic qualifiers]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nzfootball.co.nz/newsarticle/81493 |title=Buckingham names strong squad for Olympic qualifiers |publisher=New Zealand Football |date=30 August 2019 |access-date=28 July 2021}}</ref>

In 2021, Wood played in two friendlies against Australia, scoring in the first.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nzfootball.co.nz/newsarticle/105660 |title=Men's Olympic Team beat Australia 2–0 in Ichihara |publisher=New Zealand Football |date=12 July 2021 |access-date=28 July 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nzfootball.co.nz/newsarticle/105759 |title=Men's Olympic Team take positives from 1–0 defeat |publisher=New Zealand Football |date=15 July 2021 |access-date=28 July 2021}}</ref> At the [[Football at the 2020 Summer Olympics|2020 Olympics]], he played in [[Football at the 2020 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament – Group B|all three group matches]] and scored twice.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/person/pe150297/chris-wood/ |title=Chris Wood: Olympic Games 2021 Tokyo |website=worldfootball.net |publisher=HeimSpiel Medien |access-date=28 July 2021}}</ref> These 5 appearances and 3 goals take his totals to 10 appearances and 4 goals as of the match played on 28 July 2021.}}
